Fluers
======

Fluers is a native Rust reimplementation of the architecture of **Flue —
The Sandbox Agent Framework** (https://github.com/withastro/flue).

This project exists thanks to the excellent design work of the original
Flue author, **Fred K. Schott** (https://github.com/FredKSchott), and the
Astro team (https://astro.build) and its contributors. Fluers is an
independent Rust implementation of that architecture; all design credit
for the agent-harness model belongs to them.


What Fluers re-implements
-------------------------

Fluers re-implements Flue's architectural concepts from first principles
in Rust. It is **not** a line-by-line translation of the TypeScript
source:

  - The harness layer (`@flue/runtime`) is re-expressed as `fluers-runtime`.
  - The two foundational libraries Flue depends on —
    `@earendil-works/pi-agent-core` and `@earendil-works/pi-ai`, which
    have no published Rust crate — are re-implemented as `fluers-core`.

Per the Apache-2.0 license (Section 4d), derivative works must preserve
attribution. Source files that port specific behavior from a named Flue
file carry a doc comment citing the upstream path, e.g.:

    //! Mirrors Flue's `packages/runtime/src/agent.ts`.


